<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <ImplicitUsings>disable</ImplicitUsings>
    <GenerateDocumentationFile>true</GenerateDocumentationFile>
    <NoWarn>1591;1573</NoWarn>

    <AssemblyName>GearGoblin.Core</AssemblyName>
    <RootNamespace>GearGoblin.Core</RootNamespace>

    <Version>0.6.5.2</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.5.2</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.5.2</FileVersion>
    <PackageId>GearGoblin.Core</PackageId>
    <Authors>LastOnionKnight</Authors>
    <Description>Shared business-logic library for Tonberry Tactics — the web app (Blazor WASM) and the in-game plugin (Dalamud) both project-reference this library so their stat-priority tables, materia-tier values, and stat-name canonicalization don't drift. Targets netstandard2.0 for maximum compatibility with both halves (web builds on net8+, plugin builds on net10.0-windows). v0.6.5.2 ("Release Hardening") is a lockstep version bump only — no source changes to the library. The Core release.ps1 script gains a `git fetch + pull --rebase --autostash` preamble that keeps the workflow symmetric with Plugin and Web (both of which need the rebase step for non-fast-forward avoidance, particularly Plugin where the repo.json auto-bot pushes after every tag). Plugin v0.6.5.1 ("Quiet Info") is a hotfix for the /ttinfo hard-crash latent since v0.4.6 (the foreach-over-Split chat-dump pattern could marshal an empty entry into a null Utf8String.SetString source pointer and crash the game from ChatGui.UpdateQueue) and also trims the About-tab "What's New" section to the latest three releases. Web v0.6.5.1 ("Audit reads right") fixes an off-by-one in the v0.6.5 audit logic that was rendering Tier XII melds as "XI" and flagging them all as under-tier (wire Grade field is 0-indexed; web now adds 1 at the consumer). Library contents unchanged: JobPriorities (per-job stat priority for materia melding), MateriaTiers (Tier I–XII stat values), StatNames (BaseParam name canonicalization).</Description>
    <Copyright>(c) 2026 LastOnionKnight / Refia Rakkiri / Aisling O'Callaghan</Copyright>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin-Core</RepositoryUrl>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin-Core</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <PackageTags>ffxiv;gear;materia;bis;optimizer;tonberry-tactics;dalamud</PackageTags>
    <IncludeSymbols>true</IncludeSymbols>
    <SymbolPackageFormat>snupkg</SymbolPackageFormat>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
